      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Acetaminophen is generally safer for kidneys than ibuprofen, but it can indeed harm your liver if you exceed the recommended dosage. For a headache, a typical safe dose is 500mg to 1000mg every 4 to 6 hours, not to exceed 3000mg in a 24-hour period. Since you have CKD, you should still confirm this plan with a pharmacist or doctor, especially if you take other medications or have liver concerns.",
      "source": "target",
